		<td><b>Game Genie ROM hack to dump Zelda-II save state?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Blarrg,
<br />
<br />    How difficult would it be to create a custom GG rom that would simply dump the WRAM of any game to the second joypad port (assuming that the joypad were wired to a PC serial port)?
<br />
<br />    My Zelda-II game save slot #1 is corrupt, but passes the checksum.  Link gets a 1-up every 3 EXP points.  I'd love to get a dump of the WRAM before the battery dies.  The cart has done this since 1991.
<br />
<br />    I was thinking that a GG would be easier to mod than building a copynes (and maybe cheaper?).  I would just need an EPROM programmer (which costs nearly as much as a copynes).
<br />
<br />    I am fearful that in building a copynes I would accidentally destroy my NES CPU.
<br />
<br />    Your thoughts?
<br />
<br />ps- if I can dump this WRAM, I'll happily share it with the nesdev community.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


